{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> περιρρήγνῡμι</b> <br /> and <b>περιρρηγνύω</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"(1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Publicola” 6)\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>], <b>break off all round</b>, τὸν γήλοφον κύκλῳ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Critias” 113d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: frequently of clothes, <b>rend and tear off</b>, τὸν χιτωνίσκον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 19.197; τὴν χλαμύδα 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 15.33.4 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: also with <i>accusative</i> <i>person</i>, <b>strip</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Parthenius Mythographus 15.3:\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>] —<i>middle</i>, περιερρήξατο τοὺς πέπλους <b>tore off her own</b> garments, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Antonius” 77, compare 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 2.44: _absolutely_, 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “Antiquitates Judaicae” 9.7.3, 2nd c.AD: Arrianus Historicus “Anabasis” 7.24.3, 1st-2nd c.AD: Dio Chrysostomus Sophista 35.9; [γυναῖκες], περιερρηγμέναι [prev. author] 46.12:\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, with <i>aorist 2</i> -ερράγην, <i>intransitive</i> <i>perfect</i> περιέρρωγα, περιρρηγνυμένων φαρέων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 328 (Lyric poetry) \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; of the case or membrane that encloses pupa or shellfish, περιρρήγνυται τὸ κέλυφος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 551a23, compare 552a6; περιερρωγέναι τὸ ὄστρακον [prev. work] 601a13 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] (so in <i>active</i>, ἡ σχάδων.. τὸν ὑμένα περιρρήξας (sic) ἐκπέταται[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 554a30 \">Refs</a>].—<i>middle</i>, τὰ ζῷα τὰ ἐκ τῶν σκωλήκων περιρρηγνύμενα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 552a9); πέτρα περιρραγεῖσα [prev. work] 578b22 \">Refs</a>]; of dead flesh, <b>break away</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἀγμῶν” 26. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>cause</b> a stream <b>to break</b> or <b>divide round</b> a piece of land, [Βούσιρις] τὸν Νεῖλον περὶ τὴν χώραν περιέρρηξε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 11.31 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, τοῦ Δέλτα κατὰ τὸ ὀξὺ περιρρήγνυται ὁ Νεῖλος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.16, compare 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “De Natura Animalium - Ar.Byzantine Epit.” 7.24 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; βρονταὶ περιερρήγνυντο <b>kept breaking round</b> a place, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Crassus” 19. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>break</b> a thing <b>round</b> or <b>on</b> another, <b>wreck</b>, τὸ σκαφίδιον πρὸς πέτραν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Merc.Cond.” 2, compare 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 1.114; ἀλλήλοισι π. ἀέλλας 4th c.AD(?): Quintus Smyrnaeus Epicus 8.61. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> ὄρος περιερρωγός <b>broken all round</b>, i.e. <b>precipitous</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Nicolaus Damascenus Historicus 1 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G4048","accentedUnicode":"περιρρήγνυμι","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G4012","matchingForm":"περί","stepTransliteration":"peri","gloss":"about","_zh_tw_Gloss":"為, 關於","_es_Gloss":"acerca de","_zh_Gloss":"为, 关于"},{"strongNumber":"G4486","matchingForm":"ῥήγνυμι","stepTransliteration":"rēgnumi","gloss":"to throw violently","_zh_tw_Gloss":"裂開","_es_Gloss":"tirar violentamente","_zh_Gloss":"裂开"}],"shortDef":"to strip off, tear off","mediumDef":"also spelled <greek>περιρρήγνυμι</greek>, <b>to break</b> or <